newsitem.title: USA: US Treasury 5-yr note sale seen yielding 6.555 pct.
newsitem.headline: US Treasury 5-yr note sale seen yielding 6.555 pct.

text.p: The U.S. Treasury's auction of $12.5 billion in five-year notes on Wednesday is expected to produce a yield near 6.555 percent, dealers said.
At 1245 EDT/1645 GMT, the five-year notes were quoted at 6.525 percent in when-issued trade. The bidding deadline for the notes is 1300 EDT/1700 GMT and results are expected around 1345 EDT/1745 GMT.
